# 9) Update / redeploy workflow

### 9.1 Backend server update

```bash
cd ~/Gradion
git pull
docker compose -f docker-compose.yml -f docker-compose.backend.yml up -d --build
docker compose logs backend --tail 20
```

Migrations run automatically on backend startup. To seed test users (production image):

```bash
docker compose exec backend sh -lc "npm run prisma:seed:prod"
```

If the backend is restarting, use a one-off container:

```bash
docker compose run --rm --no-deps backend npm run prisma:seed:prod
```

### 9.2 Frontend server update

```bash
cd ~/Gradion
git pull
cd frontend
docker build -t gradion-frontend:prod -f Dockerfile .
docker rm -f gradion-frontend
docker run -d \
  --name gradion-frontend \
  --restart unless-stopped \
  -p 5050:3000 \
  gradion-frontend:prod
docker ps --filter name=gradion-frontend
curl -s -o /dev/null -w "%{http_code}\n" http://127.0.0.1:5050
```

If you see `502 Bad Gateway`, the frontend container is usually **not running** (check `docker ps -a`). A common mistake is an incomplete `docker run` line, e.g. `--restart` without `unless-stopped`.

Ensure `frontend/.env.local` exists **before** `docker build` (e.g. `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=https://api.gradion.id/api`).

